This assessment documents the redaction invariant for future observability work: structured/status logging may remain, but request headers, `Cookie` values, Bearer tokens, Claude session keys, ChatGPT session cookies, tr
S05 should consume findings 1 and 4 first. Implement replace-not-display credential settings flows where practical, prevent saved ChatGPT cookie values from rehydrating into editable text fields, clear raw credential `@S
S07 should treat this report as the logging contract. Existing structured/status logging may continue, but any new HTTP/provider/WebView diagnostics must pass through a redactor and include tests proving request headers,
### M002 Handoff
M002 should own durable credential redesign: Keychain-backed ChatGPT storage, replace-only credential UX, explicit Claude Keychain migration if service identifiers change, and runtime WebView/cookie cleanup verification.
- S03 is a review and invariant-hardening slice, not a durable credential remediation slice.
- WebView cookie/session cleanup still needs runtime verification in a follow-up or M002.
- Redaction tests currently cover user-facing error descriptions and credential-free settings persistence; future logging/redactor surfaces need their own tests before diagnostics expand.
- No real credentials were used; all test sentinels are synthetic and intentionally nonfunctional.

